# client_guardrails.me
# Purpose: Strict rules for iOS and Android clients. Defines what clients can and
#          cannot do. These constraints exist to maintain data integrity, prevent
#          security bypass, and ensure consistent product behaviour.
# Scope: iOS (SwiftUI), Android (Jetpack Compose or equivalent)

---

## 1. NETWORK AND DATA

### DO
- Include every required column in PostgREST `select=` strings (see data_contracts.me).
- Lowercase all UUID values before passing to PostgREST filters.
- Decode Supabase timestamps using the project-standard date parser (not raw Codable `Date?`).
- Sanitise all text fields received from Supabase at decode time: apply length caps, validate URL schemes.
- Use the anon key for Edge Function calls (`apikey` and `Authorization` headers). User JWT is for PostgREST DB calls only.
- Handle HTTP 204 (No Content) responses without throwing — some RPCs return no body.
- Handle HTTP 409 (Conflict) specifically for duplicate review submissions — show "already reviewed" message, not a generic error.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT pass unbounded Supabase text fields directly into UI models without length capping.
- Do NOT use `bookadink-preset://` URL scheme for anything — deprecated and blocked.
- Do NOT call Edge Functions with the user JWT as the Authorization header.
- Do NOT rely on PostgREST schema cache for newly created RPCs (PGRST202). Use direct PATCH/INSERT instead for `use_credits` and `issue_cancellation_credit` flows.
- Do NOT assume a query returned 0 rows means "not found" — always verify network errors separately.

---

## 2. BOOKING AND PAYMENT

### DO
- Insert a booking row only after Stripe PaymentSheet returns `.completed` (or game is free / full credit cover).
- Pass `nil` (not `0`) for `creditsAppliedCents` when no credits are applied to `requestBooking`.
- Always include `clubID` when calling `confirmPendingBooking` — both iOS call sites must pass this.
- Refresh credit balance at the top of `preparePaymentSheet` before computing the net amount.
- Display live hold countdown from `booking.holdExpiresAt`. Update every second.
- Show "Spot hold expired" passive state when `holdExpiresAt <= now()`. Do NOT auto-retry promotion.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT compute platform fee on the client. Fee comes from Edge Function response.
- Do NOT insert a booking on Stripe `.canceled` or `.failed`.
- Do NOT decrement credits on Stripe `.canceled` or `.failed`.
- Do NOT allow booking a game where `publishAt > now()` from the player booking flow.
- Do NOT allow a player to hold more than one `confirmed` or `pending_payment` seat per game.
- Do NOT call `confirmPendingBooking` without `clubID`.

---

## 3. CREDITS

### DO
- Use `creditBalanceByClubID: [UUID: Int]` (club-scoped dictionary) for all credit operations.
- Optimistic update: decrement `creditBalanceByClubID[clubID]` immediately on main thread; confirm with DB value after background operation.
- Show credit toggle only when: `game.fee > 0 AND creditBalance(for: clubID) > 0 AND canBook`.
- Refresh credit balance after cancellation to compute the credited amount and trigger UI update.
- Compute net price inline as: `max(0, totalFee - min(balance, totalFee))`.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT use a global (non-club-scoped) `creditBalanceCents: Int` — deprecated.
- Do NOT call `use_credits` or `issue_cancellation_credit` RPCs via PostgREST — PGRST202 failure.
- Do NOT allow credits to go below 0. The PATCH atomic guard handles this server-side; the client should also guard against displaying negative values.
- Do NOT apply credits from Club A to a booking at Club B.

---

## 4. CLUB DATA

### DO
- Load club data on tab change only (not on view appear unconditionally).
- Include `latitude` and `longitude` in all 5 club select strings.
- Use `String.normalizedAddress()` to display club addresses (trim, collapse whitespace, title-case, max 40 chars).
- Validate custom image URLs against allowed Supabase host before rendering.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT use `confirmationDialog("Club Actions", ...)` in ClubDetailView — caused production freeze.
- Do NOT use `containerRelativeFrame` or forced clipping in club navigation containers.
- Do NOT trigger network tasks automatically on ClubDetailView open — load on tab change only.
- Do NOT pass unbounded Supabase text fields to UI models.

---

## 5. LAYOUT AND UI

### DO
- Apply `.frame(maxWidth: .infinity)` to every card/container before `.background(...)`.
- Cap avatar preview rows with `prefix(N)` where N satisfies the row width constraint.
- Show overflow as a `+N` badge — never as additional circles.
- For screens with vertical scroll, always constrain root container to viewport width.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT use `.fixedSize(horizontal: true)` on any view — causes overflow on narrow devices.
- Do NOT add `ScrollView(.horizontal)` inside full-page vertical scrolls without explicit width bounding.
- Do NOT use `frame(minWidth: X)` on container views unless X < available content width.
- Do NOT feed `GeometryReader` size values back into child frame widths (read-only use only).
- Do NOT use `.blendMode(.screen)` on SVG assets with transparent backgrounds.

