## 6. NAVIGATION AND NOTIFICATIONS

### DO
- Use a dedicated back stack for the Notifications screen. Club destinations push inline; game destinations open as bottom sheets.
- Show chevron indicator on notification rows only when `hasDestination: true`.
- Review notifications are always tappable. They do NOT require the game to be in memory.
- Extract game title from review notification using the "How was {title}?" prefix strip.
- **Refresh notifications on foreground return** — in the Android `Activity.onResume` or `Lifecycle.ON_RESUME` observer, call the notification refresh function. This keeps the in-app inbox, tab badge, and app icon badge all in sync without requiring a manual pull-to-refresh.
- **Sync app icon badge** — after every notification refresh, mark-read, mark-all-read, and clear-all: update the Android app icon badge to the current unread count. Use `NotificationManagerCompat` badge APIs or `ShortcutBadger` to set/clear the badge. Badge must read 0 when there are no unread notifications.
- **Single source of truth for unread count** — compute `unreadCount` from the in-memory notification list (filter `!is_read`). Tab badge and app icon badge both derive from this same value. Never maintain a separate counter.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT route notification taps by switching the main bottom-nav tab (e.g. switching to Clubs tab). Notifications handle their own navigation.
- Do NOT skip foreground refresh — relying on push-only updates means the badge count drifts whenever a notification is read on another device or via the web.
- Do NOT maintain separate unread counters for the tab badge and app icon badge — use one shared value.

