## 7. GAME FORMAT AND PAYMENT METHOD

### DO
- Use only the canonical `game_format` values when writing to the DB: `"open_play"`, `"random"`, `"round_robin"`, `"king_of_court"`, `"dupr_king_of_court"`. Reject any other value client-side before the network call.
- Map display labels in the UI layer only. The wire/DB value is always the canonical string — never derive it from a display label.
- Use only the canonical `payment_method` values: `"stripe"`, `"admin"`, `"cash"`, `"credits"`, NULL. Free games use NULL — not `"free"`.

### DO NOT
- Do NOT write `"ladder"` as a `game_format` — it was a legacy alias for `"king_of_court"` and has been normalised out. The DB CHECK constraint will reject it.
- Do NOT write `"free"` as a `payment_method` — it was normalised to NULL. The DB CHECK constraint will reject it.
- Do NOT label `curr_credits_returned_cents` in analytics as "Refunded" or "Cash Refunded" — the correct label is **"Credits Returned"** (club credit exposure, not a Stripe cash refund).

